1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:03,336
[Omar] <i>What's happening</i>
<i>in our country is truly sad.</i>

2
00:00:03,420 --> 00:00:06,172
<i>Even sadder,</i>
<i>instead of finding a solution,</i>

3
00:00:06,256 --> 00:00:07,966
<i>people are becoming increasingly divided.</i>

4
00:00:08,049 --> 00:00:11,928
[Marcus] <i>The longer it takes me to find</i>
<i>and break up that syndicate,</i>

5
00:00:12,011 --> 00:00:14,180
the more people will die.

6
00:00:14,264 --> 00:00:17,142
What matters is that you're not giving up.

7
00:00:17,225 --> 00:00:20,979
<i>I know you won't stop</i>
<i>until you complete your mission.</i>

8
00:00:21,062 --> 00:00:23,523
Sir, I don't think Reyes is one of them.

9
00:00:23,606 --> 00:00:26,067
[Jalil] <i>He's also on a quest</i>
<i>to uncover what really happened</i>

10
00:00:26,151 --> 00:00:26,943
<i>on the island.</i>

11
00:00:27,027 --> 00:00:29,237
[Marcus] <i>Since I'm not getting</i>
<i>an answer from you,</i>

12
00:00:29,320 --> 00:00:31,740
<i>I'll find the truth another way.</i>

13
00:00:31,823 --> 00:00:32,991
What about his colleagues?

14
00:00:33,074 --> 00:00:34,617
I'm still investigating them.

15
00:00:34,701 --> 00:00:36,786
[Jalil] <i>What exactly happened</i>
<i>on Damai Island?</i>

16
00:00:36,870 --> 00:00:38,329
Why did it all turn into chaos?

17
00:00:38,413 --> 00:00:40,498
Someone came on the radio. They said…

18
00:00:40,582 --> 00:00:42,125
[man, in English] <i>Neutralize the area!</i>

19
00:00:42,208 --> 00:00:43,460
<i>There are no civilians there!</i>

20
00:00:43,543 --> 00:00:44,461
<i>It's an ambush!</i>

21
00:00:44,544 --> 00:00:46,504
Who was on the other line?

22
00:00:46,588 --> 00:00:47,422
[Suarez] <i>I don't know, sir.</i>

23
00:00:47,505 --> 00:00:48,715
I didn't hear them, anyway.

24
00:00:48,798 --> 00:00:50,675
Well, who received those messages?

25
00:00:51,384 --> 00:00:53,052
The people close to Sir Marcus.

26
00:00:53,136 --> 00:00:54,679
Also, those in command.

27
00:00:55,847 --> 00:00:57,057
Including Ma'am Lara.

28
00:00:57,140 --> 00:00:58,433
[Azuelo] <i>Good thing you're here.</i>

29
00:00:58,516 --> 00:01:00,435
Agent Reyes is on official leave.

30
00:01:00,518 --> 00:01:03,646
<i>You'll be partnering with Agent Angeles</i>
<i>for the time being.</i>

31
00:01:05,148 --> 00:01:07,859
[Jalil] <i>Were you involved</i>
<i>in what happened back home?</i>

32
00:01:07,942 --> 00:01:10,487
<i>I'll find out your secret.</i>

33
00:01:10,570 --> 00:01:13,948
[Usman] <i>I hope you find the answer</i>
<i>on the island, brother.</i>

34
00:01:14,032 --> 00:01:17,202
<i>Bring justice to the deaths</i>
<i>of our colleagues.</i>

35
00:01:17,994 --> 00:01:19,496
[tense music playing]

36
00:01:20,205 --> 00:01:22,373
[Marcus] <i>It all started on this island.</i>

37
00:01:22,457 --> 00:01:25,335
<i>I know I'll find the answer here.</i>

38
00:01:29,881 --> 00:01:35,053
[mysterious theme music playing]

39
00:01:45,396 --> 00:01:50,401
[stirring music playing]

40
00:02:09,420 --> 00:02:13,883
[stirring music continues]

41
00:02:32,277 --> 00:02:35,947
[stirring music continues]

42
00:02:54,632 --> 00:02:57,886
[stirring music continues]

43
00:03:12,901 --> 00:03:16,321
[stirring music continues]

44
00:03:16,404 --> 00:03:19,532
[birds chirping]

45
00:03:19,616 --> 00:03:23,870
[leaves crunching]

46
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:37,217
[stirring music continues]

47
00:03:51,773 --> 00:03:53,024
[in English] Stop.

48
00:04:03,993 --> 00:04:09,582
[stirring music continues]

49
00:04:20,635 --> 00:04:23,388
[stirring music continues]

50
00:04:30,353 --> 00:04:33,564
[music intensifying]

51
00:04:35,900 --> 00:04:40,113
[music fading]

52
00:04:40,196 --> 00:04:41,823
[high-pitched device whine]

53
00:04:41,906 --> 00:04:44,117
[gloomy music playing]

54
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:46,077
[electronic whining]

55
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:46,995
‪[bird chirping]

56
00:05:00,550 --> 00:05:05,888
[gloomy music continues]

57
00:05:09,976 --> 00:05:12,437
[suspenseful music playing]

58
00:05:59,150 --> 00:06:01,194
[thrilling music playing]

59
00:06:01,277 --> 00:06:02,904
- Dad.
- Lara.

60
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:08,951
We're heading into the next stage
of our plan, Lara.

61
00:06:12,121 --> 00:06:15,875
[in English] I hope you are
in the right state of mind.

62
00:06:15,958 --> 00:06:18,044
[thrilling music continues]

63
00:06:18,127 --> 00:06:19,253
[in English] Of course, Dad.

64
00:06:22,173 --> 00:06:23,466
[breathes deeply]

65
00:06:24,092 --> 00:06:25,218
- Gen.
- Hmm.

66
00:06:25,718 --> 00:06:27,220
Lara was followed.

67
00:06:27,929 --> 00:06:28,930
[in English] What?

68
00:06:30,223 --> 00:06:35,686
[thrilling music continues]

69
00:06:46,114 --> 00:06:47,782
[gunshots]

70
00:06:50,159 --> 00:06:53,037
[pensive music playing]

71
00:06:59,544 --> 00:07:00,920
[rapid gunfire]

72
00:07:01,003 --> 00:07:02,004
[child whimpers]

73
00:07:02,630 --> 00:07:04,632
[Marcus] <i>From the trajectory</i>
<i>of the bullets…</i>

74
00:07:05,424 --> 00:07:07,135
<i>that's where the shots came from.</i>

75
00:07:08,177 --> 00:07:11,055
[gunshots]

76
00:07:11,139 --> 00:07:12,974
[grunting]

77
00:07:16,811 --> 00:07:20,606
[unsettling music playing]

78
00:07:32,326 --> 00:07:33,327
[knocking on car window]

79
00:07:33,411 --> 00:07:34,912
[car window whirring]

80
00:07:36,247 --> 00:07:37,874
[in English] Sir, positive.

81
00:07:37,957 --> 00:07:39,709
Is there a problem, sir?

82
00:07:39,792 --> 00:07:41,502
They want you to come inside, right now.

83
00:07:42,795 --> 00:07:47,383
[unsettling music continues]

84
00:07:47,467 --> 00:07:48,509
[car door clicks open]

85
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:58,811
Surrender your gun.

86
00:08:03,149 --> 00:08:04,317
That's not going to happen.

87
00:08:04,984 --> 00:08:09,030
[unsettling music continues]

88
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:13,284
[grunts and groans]

89
00:08:13,367 --> 00:08:15,536
- Do it!
- [grunting]

90
00:08:15,620 --> 00:08:17,580
- Give it a try!
- [grunting, groaning]

91
00:08:20,708 --> 00:08:22,460
What's going on here?!

92
00:08:23,169 --> 00:08:25,129
[man grunting, groaning]

93
00:08:25,213 --> 00:08:26,047
‪[music intensifies]

94
00:08:27,673 --> 00:08:28,883
[groans]

95
00:08:30,468 --> 00:08:35,264
[tense music playing]

96
00:08:40,186 --> 00:08:41,854
[birds chirping]

97
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:47,151
[pensive music playing]

98
00:08:59,372 --> 00:09:00,623
[music intensifies]

99
00:09:00,706 --> 00:09:06,045
[tense music playing]

100
00:09:23,271 --> 00:09:27,441
[tense music continues]

101
00:09:45,376 --> 00:09:50,756
[tense music continues]

102
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:53,467
[rapid gunfire]

103
00:10:04,228 --> 00:10:09,317
[tense music continues]

104
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:16,907
[leaves rustling]

105
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:34,050
[morose music playing]

106
00:10:52,026 --> 00:10:58,282
[morose music continues]

107
00:11:06,374 --> 00:11:10,169
What are you doing in front of my house?

108
00:11:11,379 --> 00:11:13,714
[in English] Are you spying on me?

109
00:11:16,384 --> 00:11:19,720
[morose music continues]

110
00:11:21,138 --> 00:11:24,809
[in English]
Police General Manuel Carillo.

111
00:11:26,811 --> 00:11:29,814
[in English] Retired, but still respected.

112
00:11:30,398 --> 00:11:34,777
His influence in SID
and NLEA is still strong.

113
00:11:34,860 --> 00:11:39,156
Aside from that,
his protégé is the head agent,

114
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:40,491
Lara Angeles.

115
00:11:41,325 --> 00:11:43,035
I'm just doing my job, sir.

116
00:11:43,536 --> 00:11:46,705
[sinister music playing]

117
00:11:49,333 --> 00:11:50,543
And…

118
00:11:52,294 --> 00:11:54,672
what is your job?

119
00:11:57,675 --> 00:11:59,510
Be careful with this one.

120
00:11:59,593 --> 00:12:01,095
He's sharp.

121
00:12:01,178 --> 00:12:02,972
One look at you,

122
00:12:03,055 --> 00:12:05,015
and he already knows
what your intentions are.

123
00:12:05,099 --> 00:12:07,017
He's good at reading people.

124
00:12:07,101 --> 00:12:08,644
[unsettling music playing]

125
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:14,775
Since when did it become your job

126
00:12:14,859 --> 00:12:17,194
to spy outside my house?

127
00:12:18,237 --> 00:12:19,321
[Manuel] Hmm?

128
00:12:19,405 --> 00:12:20,823
Sir, this wasn't in the plan.

129
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:24,201
I just followed my instinct.

130
00:12:28,914 --> 00:12:29,999
Hmm.

131
00:12:30,791 --> 00:12:32,334
Espina.

132
00:12:34,128 --> 00:12:39,633
[in English] Police Major Allan Espina.

133
00:12:40,468 --> 00:12:41,343
Am I right?

134
00:12:42,470 --> 00:12:43,596
[Manuel] Hmm.

135
00:12:43,679 --> 00:12:45,347
I only heard about you now.

136
00:12:46,515 --> 00:12:48,309
What batch are you from?

137
00:12:48,392 --> 00:12:53,022
Sir, isn't all my information
in the official records?

138
00:12:53,105 --> 00:12:57,735
I already checked all your files.

139
00:12:58,402 --> 00:13:01,572
Almost everything is redacted.

140
00:13:02,323 --> 00:13:05,326
[tense music playing]

141
00:13:10,372 --> 00:13:14,043
Remember. If there's anyone
you should be careful with,

142
00:13:14,710 --> 00:13:15,878
it's him.

143
00:13:15,961 --> 00:13:21,842
Because he's the only one
who can expose your true identity.

144
00:13:22,510 --> 00:13:23,636
[in English] Yes, sir.

145
00:13:24,345 --> 00:13:26,222
[in Arabic] In God's care.

146
00:13:27,598 --> 00:13:30,726
There's a reason why
my records are like that, sir.

147
00:13:32,645 --> 00:13:36,190
Are you challenging me? Hmm…

148
00:13:37,107 --> 00:13:38,526
Espina?

149
00:13:39,109 --> 00:13:42,112
Remember, I can find out everything

150
00:13:42,196 --> 00:13:46,825
you're hiding if I want to.

151
00:13:47,576 --> 00:13:51,914
[tense music continues]

152
00:13:58,462 --> 00:14:00,130
I'll leave it to you, sir.

153
00:14:01,382 --> 00:14:02,758
I'm not afraid

154
00:14:04,426 --> 00:14:06,512
because I'm not hiding anything illegal.

155
00:14:06,595 --> 00:14:07,888
[Manuel] Hmm.

156
00:14:07,972 --> 00:14:09,932
Are you sure?

157
00:14:10,015 --> 00:14:13,894
[in English] No skeletons in your closet?

158
00:14:13,978 --> 00:14:16,772
Check it, so you'll know.

159
00:14:17,398 --> 00:14:21,443
[tense music continues]

160
00:14:22,027 --> 00:14:27,533
[laughing wryly]

161
00:14:28,617 --> 00:14:30,703
[breathes deeply]

162
00:14:30,786 --> 00:14:36,667
What is your intention with SID?

163
00:14:38,127 --> 00:14:39,545
Hmm?

164
00:14:40,254 --> 00:14:42,548
Like everyone else, sir.

165
00:14:43,924 --> 00:14:46,969
I just want to know the truth.

166
00:14:47,970 --> 00:14:49,471
The truth?

167
00:14:49,555 --> 00:14:50,806
[in English] Yes, sir.

168
00:14:53,601 --> 00:14:59,231
That's only for people who have
the ability to see the truth

169
00:14:59,315 --> 00:15:01,442
once it's right in front of them.

170
00:15:02,484 --> 00:15:06,739
[in English] It's not just a skill.

171
00:15:08,616 --> 00:15:10,743
[in English] It's a special gift.

172
00:15:10,826 --> 00:15:12,077
Yes, sir.

173
00:15:14,246 --> 00:15:16,790
That's why I was sent by Muslim Affairs.

174
00:15:18,667 --> 00:15:20,586
Because I'm that person.

175
00:15:20,669 --> 00:15:24,214
[tense music playing]

176
00:15:26,508 --> 00:15:28,928
Alright, sir. I'll get going.

177
00:15:29,011 --> 00:15:31,847
Sorry if I'm disturbing you.

178
00:15:32,890 --> 00:15:34,099
[in English] Sir.

179
00:15:34,975 --> 00:15:40,856
[tense music continues]

180
00:15:55,913 --> 00:16:01,126
[tense music continues]

181
00:16:01,210 --> 00:16:06,423
[pensive music playing]

182
00:16:17,017 --> 00:16:18,268
[sighs]

183
00:16:20,270 --> 00:16:22,564
[breathes deeply]

184
00:16:27,486 --> 00:16:31,991
[morose music playing]

185
00:17:25,335 --> 00:17:27,087
[Marcus] <i>I was right.</i>

186
00:17:27,796 --> 00:17:29,965
<i>There really was a group</i>
<i>that caused trouble that night.</i>

187
00:17:30,799 --> 00:17:33,343
<i>I will make sure you pay,</i>

188
00:17:33,969 --> 00:17:36,597
<i>and so will whoever is behind you.</i>

189
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:42,227
[pensive music playing]

190
00:17:42,853 --> 00:17:44,646
You're so careless!

191
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:46,648
That man followed you,

192
00:17:46,732 --> 00:17:49,193
right here to my own home!

193
00:17:49,276 --> 00:17:51,153
[exhales sharply]

194
00:17:51,236 --> 00:17:54,156
Have you forgotten everything
I taught you?!

195
00:17:54,239 --> 00:17:56,200
You weren't like this before!

196
00:17:57,076 --> 00:17:59,369
Why are you suddenly messing up now?!

197
00:17:59,453 --> 00:18:02,664
- [exhales sharply]
- [in English] I'm sorry.

198
00:18:04,166 --> 00:18:05,751
[exhales sharply]

199
00:18:07,586 --> 00:18:12,925
[glum music playing]

200
00:18:20,015 --> 00:18:23,227
[morose music playing]

201
00:18:23,310 --> 00:18:25,187
[Marcus] <i>We were set up to cause chaos</i>

202
00:18:25,270 --> 00:18:27,231
<i>the night Datu Rahman was arrested.</i>

203
00:18:28,190 --> 00:18:31,777
<i>And now they're making him out</i>
<i>to be a criminal.</i>

204
00:18:32,694 --> 00:18:33,987
<i>But for what?</i>

205
00:18:34,863 --> 00:18:37,699
<i>What's their real plan in all of this?</i>

206
00:18:39,368 --> 00:18:42,454
[footsteps approaching]

207
00:18:48,627 --> 00:18:50,879
[footsteps approaching]

208
00:18:53,841 --> 00:18:56,343
[footsteps approaching]

209
00:19:07,771 --> 00:19:09,857
[footsteps approaching]

210
00:19:10,482 --> 00:19:14,987
[morose music continues]

211
00:19:21,702 --> 00:19:27,457
[footsteps approaching]

212
00:19:31,378 --> 00:19:35,174
[tense music playing]

213
00:19:35,883 --> 00:19:41,555
[footsteps approaching]

214
00:19:47,102 --> 00:19:48,604
- [blows land]
- [groans]

215
00:20:01,909 --> 00:20:02,868
[music fades]

216
00:20:02,951 --> 00:20:08,207
[pensive music playing]

217
00:20:11,501 --> 00:20:12,711
Espina!

218
00:20:13,921 --> 00:20:15,339
[in English] How dare you.

219
00:20:15,422 --> 00:20:17,549
Why did you follow me to my daddy's house?

220
00:20:17,633 --> 00:20:18,675
Why did you do that?

221
00:20:18,759 --> 00:20:21,386
- I just want to know what you're hiding.
- [scoffs]

222
00:20:21,887 --> 00:20:23,597
Don't take it personally.

223
00:20:23,680 --> 00:20:25,557
You're not the only one I'm investigating.

224
00:20:25,641 --> 00:20:27,017
If there's anything you need to know,

225
00:20:27,100 --> 00:20:28,727
why don't you just ask straight up?

226
00:20:29,478 --> 00:20:31,104
Why, Agent Angeles?

227
00:20:31,188 --> 00:20:32,648
When you interrogate someone,

228
00:20:32,731 --> 00:20:34,608
do they tell you the truth immediately?

229
00:20:35,484 --> 00:20:37,361
[in English] Are you interrogating me?

230
00:20:37,444 --> 00:20:39,238
We'll get there.

231
00:20:40,113 --> 00:20:41,073
Don't be impatient.

232
00:20:50,791 --> 00:20:54,836
[pensive music continues]

233
00:20:57,756 --> 00:20:58,674
- [music fades]
- [birds chirping]

234
00:20:59,258 --> 00:21:00,759
[foreboding music playing]

235
00:21:00,842 --> 00:21:02,094
Harold.

236
00:21:03,553 --> 00:21:05,013
Harold, you're alive!

237
00:21:05,806 --> 00:21:06,598
[groans]

238
00:21:06,682 --> 00:21:08,475
- [Marcus groans]
- [tense music playing]

239
00:21:08,558 --> 00:21:09,393
Harold…

240
00:21:10,060 --> 00:21:11,478
What did you do to my colleagues?

241
00:21:11,561 --> 00:21:12,521
Harold…

242
00:21:12,604 --> 00:21:13,897
What did you do to my colleagues?!

243
00:21:13,981 --> 00:21:16,024
[both grunting]

244
00:21:16,108 --> 00:21:17,317
[grunts and groans]

245
00:21:22,197 --> 00:21:24,032
[grunts and groans]

246
00:21:25,909 --> 00:21:28,996
What happened to my colleagues?!

247
00:21:29,079 --> 00:21:31,123
[grunting angrily]

248
00:21:31,206 --> 00:21:36,795
[tense music continues]

249
00:21:42,175 --> 00:21:43,969
I wish they'd come back.

250
00:21:44,052 --> 00:21:47,431
[girl] <i>Jalil and Datu Rahman.</i>

251
00:21:48,015 --> 00:21:51,393
I don't trust Marcus.

252
00:21:51,476 --> 00:21:53,145
[Usman] <i>This person's life is in danger.</i>

253
00:21:53,228 --> 00:21:55,397
They're accusing him
of being your accomplice.

254
00:21:55,480 --> 00:21:57,566
[Usman] <i>So if you want to save this guy,</i>

255
00:21:57,649 --> 00:22:00,027
<i>tell us everything you know.</i>

256
00:22:00,110 --> 00:22:01,153
[tense music playing]

257
00:22:01,236 --> 00:22:02,237
[Jalil] Doctor?

258
00:22:04,239 --> 00:22:05,615
[Teresa] Have dinner at my house.

259
00:22:05,699 --> 00:22:09,119
Let me make it up to you.

260
00:22:09,202 --> 00:22:10,412
[Jalil] <i>You live alone?</i>

261
00:22:11,997 --> 00:22:12,831
[Teresa sobs]

262
00:22:12,914 --> 00:22:14,458
I'm sorry.

263
00:22:14,541 --> 00:22:18,170
